I"5<p>This exhibition of the “forgotten” Jan Dibbets Collection was organized after President of the Dutch Senate René van der Linden paid a visit in 2009 to the National Gallery of Arts at the request of Jan Dibbets to check whether the collection was still in the possession the National Gallery. (The official story told in the catalogue was that Van der Linden “accidentally” learned of the existence of the collection from then GKA Director Ruberns Shima). Van der Linden returned in October 2010, together with Jan Dibbets, to visit the exhibition.</p>
